  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Established Marine Company recruiting people to join their logistics team:</strong></p><h2><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></h2><ul><li>You will be part of the Logistics Team, responsible for planning and ensuring smooth operations for our logistics functions. </li><li>Liaise with various departments in the company to provide logistical support.</li><li>Manage and optimize warehouse space, and to ensure warehouse is well maintained & with clear stock count visuals.</li></ul><ul><li>To maintain and update supplier log for all inventory goods into the system.</li><li>Packing and unpacking of new and old goods, and to verify against accompanying paperwork.</li><li>Prepare and arrange sorting of products, packing and palletize the goods for local and export shipments.</li><li>Require to load and unload new shipments of goods</li><li>Assist the Head of Supply Chain to purchase equipment and ensure shipping is timely.</li><li>Any other ad hoc tasks as assigned</li></ul><h2><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></h2><ul><li>Singaporeans or Singapore PRs are preferred</li><li>Candidates must possess at least a diploma in any field.</li><li>Knowledge of Microsoft Word/Excel and IT Skills are required.</li><li>Must possess good communication, inter-personal skills.</li><li>There will be an added advantage for candidates with work experience in the marine industry.</li><li>Fresh graduates who are interested in the maritime industry are welcome to apply.</li></ul><p>Interested candidates please email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:career@cantrade.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">career@cantrade.com.sg</a> </p><p>To facilitate the recruitment process, please include your <u><strong>expected salary, last drawn salary, reason for leaving past employment and notice period</strong></u> in your resume.</p><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified about their applications.</p>",
